SOFTWARE
1.Arduino IDE (for development, can be replaced by Wokwi's built-in IDE)

2.Wokwi Simulator (https://wokwi.com/)

3.GitHub (for code versioning and project documentation)

4.draw.io / Lucidchart (for flowchart creation)

5.Screen recording software (OBS Studio, Xbox Recorder) for demo video



HARDWARE
1.Arduino Uno

2.DS3231 or DS1307 Real-Time Clock (RTC) module

3.DHT11 / DS18B20 / LM35 Temperature sensor 

4.16x2 LCD (optional, or use Serial Monitor)

5.Breadboard and connecting wires (virtual in Wokwi)

6. Add a Buzzer beep every 1 second during the over-temperature condition.

Optional Cloud Environment for Future Expansion

1.ThingSpeak / Blynk / MQTT Broker for remote monitoring

2.Cloud dashboard (AWS IoT, Azure IoT, or Google Cloud IoT Core)



